    "title": {
        "rendered": "MatR: Billy Joel and Bruce Springsteen: You May Be Right"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "<p>&#8220;You May Be Right&#8221; is one of Billy Joel&#8217;s best-known songs.</p>\n<p>The first track on and second single from his chart-topping 1980\u00a0<em>Glass Houses</em> album, &#8220;You May Be Right&#8221; peaked at #7 in the US and became a setlist staple in Billy&#8217;s still incredibly popular concerts.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe class='youtube-player' width='758' height='427' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/Jo9t5XK0FhA?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent' allowfullscreen='true' style='border:0;' sandbox='allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation'></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Almost thirty years after its release, Bruce joined Billy on stage at the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame anniversary concerts and supported him on &#8220;You May Be Right.&#8221; The performance isn&#8217;t included in the official CD or video releases, but fortunately some generous fans captured it live</p>\n<p>Check out Bruce&#8217;s one and only performance of &#8220;You May Be Right&#8221; below&#8211;the video is shaky, but the audio is clear.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe class='youtube-player' width='758' height='427' src='https://www.youtube.com/embed/Tlo9RgXg1ME?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent' allowfullscreen='true' style='border:0;' sandbox='allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation'></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>You May Be Right</strong><br />\n<strong>First performed:</strong> October 29, 2009 (New York City, NY)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> October 29, 2009 (New York City, NY)</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
        "rendered": "<p>One time only: Bruce teams up with Billy Joel on Billy&#8217;s perennial hit &#8220;You May Be Right&#8221; at the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame Anniversary Concerts.</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
